Data Validation Implemented in This Program
âœ”ï¸ 1. Name Input Validation

The name cannot be empty when creating an account.

If the user presses Enter without typing, account creation stops.

if (name.isEmpty()) {
    System.out.println("Name cannot be empty.");
    return;
}

âœ”ï¸ 2. Password Validation

Password must be at least 4 characters.

Loop continues until a valid password is entered.

if (password.length() >= 4) break;

âœ”ï¸ 3. Positive Amount Validation

Used in deposit, withdraw, and transfer.

Amount must be non-negative.

Rejects negative values and empty input.

if (v < 0) {
    System.out.println("Amount must be non-negative.");
    return -1;
}

âœ”ï¸ 4. Valid Integer Input for Account ID

Rejects non-numeric input.

Rejects empty input.

try {
    return Integer.parseInt(line);
} catch (NumberFormatException e) {
    System.out.println("Invalid number.");
}

âœ”ï¸ 5. Authentication Validation

User must enter the correct password.

if (!acc.checkPassword(password)) {
    System.out.println("Authentication failed.");
    return;
}

âœ”ï¸ 6. Withdraw / Transfer Validation

Amount must be positive.

Balance must be sufficient (No overdraft allowed).

if (amount > balance) 
    throw new IllegalArgumentException("Insufficient funds.");

âœ”ï¸ 7. Account Closure Validation

Account can only be closed if balance = 0.0

if (acc.getBalance() != 0.0) {
    System.out.println("Account must have zero balance to close...");
    return;
}

ğŸš« Invalid Data Examples Automatically Blocked
Operation	Invalid Data	Result
Create account	empty name	blocked
Password	< 4 characters	loop until valid
Deposit	negative number	rejected
Withdraw	amount > balance	rejected
Account ID	letters / spaces	rejected
Close account	remaining balance	rejected
